39class ECKeyShare : public SSLKeyShare {
40 public:
41 ECKeyShare(int nid, uint16_t group_id) : nid_(nid), group_id_(group_id) {}
42
43 uint16_t GroupID() const override { return group_id_; }
44
45 bool Offer(CBB *out) override {
46 assert(!private_key_);
47 // Set up a shared |BN_CTX| for all operations.
48 UniquePtr<BN_CTX> bn_ctx(BN_CTX_new());
49 if (!bn_ctx) {
50 return false;
51 }
52 BN_CTXScope scope(bn_ctx.get());
53
54 // Generate a private key.
55 UniquePtr<EC_GROUP> group(EC_GROUP_new_by_curve_name(nid_));
56 private_key_.reset(BN_new());
57 if (!group || !private_key_ ||
58 !BN_rand_range_ex(private_key_.get(), 1,
59 EC_GROUP_get0_order(group.get()))) {
60 return false;
61 }
62
63 // Compute the corresponding public key and serialize it.
64 UniquePtr<EC_POINT> public_key(EC_POINT_new(group.get()));
65 if (!public_key ||
66 !EC_POINT_mul(group.get(), public_key.get(), private_key_.get(), NULL,
67 NULL, bn_ctx.get()) ||
68 !EC_POINT_point2cbb(out, group.get(), public_key.get(),
69 POINT_CONVERSION_UNCOMPRESSED, bn_ctx.get())) {
70 return false;
71 }
72
73 return true;
74 }
75
76 bool Finish(Array<uint8_t> *out_secret, uint8_t *out_alert,
77 Span<const uint8_t> peer_key) override {
78 assert(private_key_);
79 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
80
81 // Set up a shared |BN_CTX| for all operations.
82 UniquePtr<BN_CTX> bn_ctx(BN_CTX_new());
83 if (!bn_ctx) {
84 return false;
85 }
86 BN_CTXScope scope(bn_ctx.get());
87
88 UniquePtr<EC_GROUP> group(EC_GROUP_new_by_curve_name(nid_));
89 if (!group) {
90 return false;
91 }
92
93 UniquePtr<EC_POINT> peer_point(EC_POINT_new(group.get()));
94 UniquePtr<EC_POINT> result(EC_POINT_new(group.get()));
95 BIGNUM *x = BN_CTX_get(bn_ctx.get());
96 if (!peer_point || !result || !x) {
97 return false;
98 }
99
100 if (peer_key.empty() || peer_key[0] != POINT_CONVERSION_UNCOMPRESSED ||
101 !EC_POINT_oct2point(group.get(), peer_point.get(), peer_key.data(),
102 peer_key.size(), bn_ctx.get())) {
103 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_ECPOINT);
104 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
105 return false;
106 }
107
108 // Compute the x-coordinate of |peer_key| * |private_key_|.
109 if (!EC_POINT_mul(group.get(), result.get(), NULL, peer_point.get(),
110 private_key_.get(), bn_ctx.get()) ||
111 !EC_POINT_get_affine_coordinates_GFp(group.get(), result.get(), x, NULL,
112 bn_ctx.get())) {
113 return false;
114 }
115
116 // Encode the x-coordinate left-padded with zeros.
117 Array<uint8_t> secret;
118 if (!secret.Init((EC_GROUP_get_degree(group.get()) + 7) / 8) ||
119 !BN_bn2bin_padded(secret.data(), secret.size(), x)) {
120 return false;
121 }
122
123 *out_secret = std::move(secret);
124 return true;
125 }
126
127 bool SerializePrivateKey(CBB *out) override {
128 assert(private_key_);
129 UniquePtr<EC_GROUP> group(EC_GROUP_new_by_curve_name(nid_));
130 // Padding is added to avoid leaking the length.
131 size_t len = BN_num_bytes(EC_GROUP_get0_order(group.get()));
132 return BN_bn2cbb_padded(out, len, private_key_.get());
133 }
134
135 bool DeserializePrivateKey(CBS *in) override {
136 assert(!private_key_);
137 private_key_.reset(BN_bin2bn(CBS_data(in), CBS_len(in), nullptr));
138 return private_key_ != nullptr;
139 }
140
141 private:
142 UniquePtr<BIGNUM> private_key_;
143 int nid_;
144 uint16_t group_id_;
145};
146
147class X25519KeyShare : public SSLKeyShare {
148 public:
149 X25519KeyShare() {}
150
151 uint16_t GroupID() const override { return SSL_CURVE_X25519; }
152
153 bool Offer(CBB *out) override {
154 uint8_t public_key[32];
155 X25519_keypair(public_key, private_key_);
156 return !!CBB_add_bytes(out, public_key, sizeof(public_key));
157 }
158
159 bool Finish(Array<uint8_t> *out_secret, uint8_t *out_alert,
160 Span<const uint8_t> peer_key) override {
161 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
162
163 Array<uint8_t> secret;
164 if (!secret.Init(32)) {
165 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
166 return false;
167 }
168
169 if (peer_key.size() != 32 ||
170 !X25519(secret.data(), private_key_, peer_key.data())) {
171 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
172 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_ECPOINT);
173 return false;
174 }
175
176 *out_secret = std::move(secret);
177 return true;
178 }
179
180 bool SerializePrivateKey(CBB *out) override {
181 return CBB_add_bytes(out, private_key_, sizeof(private_key_));
182 }
183
184 bool DeserializePrivateKey(CBS *in) override {
185 if (CBS_len(in) != sizeof(private_key_) ||
186 !CBS_copy_bytes(in, private_key_, sizeof(private_key_))) {
187 return false;
188 }
189 return true;
190 }
191
192 private:
193 uint8_t private_key_[32];
194};
195
196class CECPQ2KeyShare : public SSLKeyShare {
197 public:
198 CECPQ2KeyShare() {}
199
200 uint16_t GroupID() const override { return SSL_CURVE_CECPQ2; }
201
202 bool Offer(CBB *out) override {
203 uint8_t x25519_public_key[32];
204 X25519_keypair(x25519_public_key, x25519_private_key_);
205
206 uint8_t hrss_entropy[HRSS_GENERATE_KEY_BYTES];
207 HRSS_public_key hrss_public_key;
208 RAND_bytes(hrss_entropy, sizeof(hrss_entropy));
209 HRSS_generate_key(&hrss_public_key, &hrss_private_key_, hrss_entropy);
210
211 uint8_t hrss_public_key_bytes[HRSS_PUBLIC_KEY_BYTES];
212 HRSS_marshal_public_key(hrss_public_key_bytes, &hrss_public_key);
213
214 if (!CBB_add_bytes(out, x25519_public_key, sizeof(x25519_public_key)) ||
215 !CBB_add_bytes(out, hrss_public_key_bytes,
216 sizeof(hrss_public_key_bytes))) {
217 return false;
218 }
219
220 return true;
221 }
222
223 bool Accept(CBB *out_public_key, Array<uint8_t> *out_secret,
224 uint8_t *out_alert, Span<const uint8_t> peer_key) override {
225 Array<uint8_t> secret;
226 if (!secret.Init(32 + HRSS_KEY_BYTES)) {
227 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
228 return false;
229 }
230
231 uint8_t x25519_public_key[32];
232 X25519_keypair(x25519_public_key, x25519_private_key_);
233
234 HRSS_public_key peer_public_key;
235 if (peer_key.size() != 32 + HRSS_PUBLIC_KEY_BYTES ||
236 !HRSS_parse_public_key(&peer_public_key, peer_key.data() + 32) ||
237 !X25519(secret.data(), x25519_private_key_, peer_key.data())) {
238 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
239 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_ECPOINT);
240 return false;
241 }
242
243 uint8_t ciphertext[HRSS_CIPHERTEXT_BYTES];
244 uint8_t entropy[HRSS_ENCAP_BYTES];
245 RAND_bytes(entropy, sizeof(entropy));
246 HRSS_encap(ciphertext, secret.data() + 32, &peer_public_key, entropy);
247
248 if (!CBB_add_bytes(out_public_key, x25519_public_key,
249 sizeof(x25519_public_key)) ||
250 !CBB_add_bytes(out_public_key, ciphertext, sizeof(ciphertext))) {
251 return false;
252 }
253
254 *out_secret = std::move(secret);
255 return true;
256 }
257
258 bool Finish(Array<uint8_t> *out_secret, uint8_t *out_alert,
259 Span<const uint8_t> peer_key) override {
260 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
261
262 Array<uint8_t> secret;
263 if (!secret.Init(32 + HRSS_KEY_BYTES)) {
264 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
265 return false;
266 }
267
268 if (peer_key.size() != 32 + HRSS_CIPHERTEXT_BYTES ||
269 !X25519(secret.data(), x25519_private_key_, peer_key.data())) {
270 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
271 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_ECPOINT);
272 return false;
273 }
274
275 HRSS_decap(secret.data() + 32, &hrss_private_key_, peer_key.data() + 32,
276 peer_key.size() - 32);
277
278 *out_secret = std::move(secret);
279 return true;
280 }
281
282 private:
283 uint8_t x25519_private_key_[32];
284 HRSS_private_key hrss_private_key_;
285};
286
287CONSTEXPR_ARRAY NamedGroup kNamedGroups[] = {
288 {NID_secp224r1, SSL_CURVE_SECP224R1, "P-224", "secp224r1"},
289 {NID_X9_62_prime256v1, SSL_CURVE_SECP256R1, "P-256", "prime256v1"},
290 {NID_secp384r1, SSL_CURVE_SECP384R1, "P-384", "secp384r1"},
291 {NID_secp521r1, SSL_CURVE_SECP521R1, "P-521", "secp521r1"},
292 {NID_X25519, SSL_CURVE_X25519, "X25519", "x25519"},
293 {NID_CECPQ2, SSL_CURVE_CECPQ2, "CECPQ2", "CECPQ2"},
294};
295
296} // namespace
297
298Span<const NamedGroup> NamedGroups() {
299 return MakeConstSpan(kNamedGroups, OPENSSL_ARRAY_SIZE(kNamedGroups));
300}
301
302UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare> SSLKeyShare::Create(uint16_t group_id) {
303 switch (group_id) {
304 case SSL_CURVE_SECP224R1:
305 return UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare>(
306 New<ECKeyShare>(NID_secp224r1, SSL_CURVE_SECP224R1));
307 case SSL_CURVE_SECP256R1:
308 return UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare>(
309 New<ECKeyShare>(NID_X9_62_prime256v1, SSL_CURVE_SECP256R1));
310 case SSL_CURVE_SECP384R1:
311 return UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare>(
312 New<ECKeyShare>(NID_secp384r1, SSL_CURVE_SECP384R1));
313 case SSL_CURVE_SECP521R1:
314 return UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare>(
315 New<ECKeyShare>(NID_secp521r1, SSL_CURVE_SECP521R1));
316 case SSL_CURVE_X25519:
317 return UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare>(New<X25519KeyShare>());
318 case SSL_CURVE_CECPQ2:
319 return UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare>(New<CECPQ2KeyShare>());
320 default:
321 return nullptr;
322 }
323}
324
325UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare> SSLKeyShare::Create(CBS *in) {
326 uint64_t group;
327 CBS private_key;
328 if (!CBS_get_asn1_uint64(in, &group) || group > 0xffff ||
329 !CBS_get_asn1(in, &private_key, CBS_ASN1_OCTETSTRING)) {
330 return nullptr;
331 }
332 UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare> key_share = Create(static_cast<uint16_t>(group));
333 if (!key_share || !key_share->DeserializePrivateKey(&private_key)) {
334 return nullptr;
335 }
336 return key_share;
337}
338
339bool SSLKeyShare::Serialize(CBB *out) {
340 CBB private_key;
341 if (!CBB_add_asn1_uint64(out, GroupID()) ||
342 !CBB_add_asn1(out, &private_key, CBS_ASN1_OCTETSTRING) ||
343 !SerializePrivateKey(&private_key) || //
344 !CBB_flush(out)) {
345 return false;
346 }
347 return true;
348}
349
350bool SSLKeyShare::Accept(CBB *out_public_key, Array<uint8_t> *out_secret,
351 uint8_t *out_alert, Span<const uint8_t> peer_key) {
352 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
353 return Offer(out_public_key) &&
354 Finish(out_secret, out_alert, peer_key);
355}
356
357bool ssl_nid_to_group_id(uint16_t *out_group_id, int nid) {
358 for (const auto &group : kNamedGroups) {
359 if (group.nid == nid) {
360 *out_group_id = group.group_id;
361 return true;
362 }
363 }
364 return false;
365}
366
367bool ssl_name_to_group_id(uint16_t *out_group_id, const char *name, size_t len) {
368 for (const auto &group : kNamedGroups) {
369 if (len == strlen(group.name) &&
370 !strncmp(group.name, name, len)) {
371 *out_group_id = group.group_id;
372 return true;
373 }
374 if (len == strlen(group.alias) &&
375 !strncmp(group.alias, name, len)) {
376 *out_group_id = group.group_id;
377 return true;
378 }
379 }
380 return false;
381}

385using namespace bssl;
386
387const char* SSL_get_curve_name(uint16_t group_id) {
388 for (const auto &group : kNamedGroups) {
389 if (group.group_id == group_id) {
390 return group.name;
391 }
392 }
393 return nullptr;
394}
